<HEADLINE>
Charges read against Jackson for first time
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
SANTA MARIA, California, Feb 28
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Trial Judge Rodney 
Melville on Monday unveiled for the first time details of the 
charges of child molestation and conspiracy charges against pop icon 
Michael Jackson. 
</P>
<P>
Before opening statements in the trial began, Melville read the 
nine-page indictment that accused Jackson of sexually molsting a 
13-year-old boy at his Neverland Ranch between February 3 and March 
3, 2003.
</P>
